data.description: Historic home on Heard Avenue! This home was originally built in 1906 and has been exceptionally well maintained, while keeping some of its historic features intact. The welcoming, covered front porch welcomes you into this great home through the foyer and into the living room. The living room is the only room in the home featuring a fireplace and built ins. The living room leads to the formal dining room, which then flows to the office/flex room or kitchen. The kitchen features stainless steel appliances, including the built-in microwave, oven and dishwasher! There is a sitting area off the kitchen that provides for continued communication and entertainment, as well as the kitchen flowing to the large breakfast room. Just off the breakfast room you will find the laundry room as well. The owner suite is on this same end of the home featuring a tray ceiling, 2 closets, and full private bathroom. The bathroom features his/her vanity spaces with sinks, a soaking tub, and separate tile shower. The remaining 2 bedrooms and a full bathroom are located at the front end of the home. Outside you will find an unattached 2 car garage, as well as a parking pad area. This home is a rare find and in a central area of Augusta close to downtown, Augusta University campuses, restaurants, hospitals, and much more. Make sure you schedule your personal tour today and view all that this home has to offer!
